## The Integrated Monitoring Stack — How the Three Tools Work Together

The three tools form a coherent monitoring architecture:

Config is the foundation — it evaluates resource configurations against defined standards and generates the raw compliance findings. Config is also the primary evidence source for Audit Manager.

Security Hub is the aggregation layer — it ingests Config findings alongside GuardDuty threat detections and Inspector vulnerability findings, normalizes them into a common format, prioritizes them by severity, and presents the ISSO with a unified view. The daily ISSO review happens in Security Hub, not in each individual service.

Audit Manager is the documentation layer — it organizes the evidence from Config (and other sources) into a compliance framework structure that supports the formal assessment and re-authorization process. Rather than the ISSO manually compiling compliance evidence before an assessment, Audit Manager maintains a continuously updated evidence library.

Together: Config detects a NON_COMPLIANT finding → Security Hub displays it as a finding with severity and remediation guidance → the ISSO acts on it → the remediation is recorded in Security Hub → Audit Manager collects evidence of the control's compliant state after remediation.

